      "content": [
        {
          "anchor": "discussion",
          "level": 2,
          "text": "Discussion",
          "type": "heading"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "A clearcoat is a separate layer of transparent specular highlights",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "used to simulate a clear transparent coating, like the paint on a",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "car, or the surface of lacquered objects. When you enable clearcoat",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "rendering for a material, RealityKit renders the clearcoat as a",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "separate layer just above the surface of the entity. You can specify",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "a clearcoat roughness value for the clearcoat to indicate how much",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "the clearcoat scatters light that bounces off of it, which softens",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "and spreads out the highlights.",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "This initializer creates an object that specifies the clearcoat",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "roughness for a material that uses the",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.RealityKit/documentation/RealityKit/CustomMaterial/clearcoatRoughness-swift.property",
              "isActive": true,
              "type": "reference"
            },
            {
              "text": " property from a",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.RealityKit/documentation/RealityKit/CustomMaterial",
              "isActive": true,
              "type": "reference"
            },
            {
              "text": " object.",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
